                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="86229" author="pjones" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2014 16:41:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok, so this was tracked under &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4416&quot; title=&quot;support for 3.12 linux kernel&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4416&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4416&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5058&quot; title=&quot;support for linux process namespace is broken&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5058&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5058&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86223" author="bogl" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2014 16:20:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;agreed.  with the landing of &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10161&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10161&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10325&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10325&lt;/a&gt; I think this can be closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86222" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2014 16:09:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now that &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10161&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10161&lt;/a&gt; has been merged do we need to keep this tick open? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="82535" author="bogl" created="Fri, 25 Apr 2014 18:55:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m fairly certain that we do in fact need a patch to extend the namespace changes done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4476&quot; title=&quot;Add support for linux process namespace&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4476&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4476&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; into server code.  In some experimental builds on future kernels I&apos;m working around the lack of such changes by config&apos;ing server kernels with CONFIG_UIDGID_STRICT_TYPE_CHECKS turned off, but that&apos;s not a good production solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was assuming that &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4476&quot; title=&quot;Add support for linux process namespace&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4476&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4476&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was going to be held open and a follow on patch for server code would be coming along eventually from James Simmons, who did the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4476&quot; title=&quot;Add support for linux process namespace&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4476&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4476&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; changes for clients.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
